{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"The future, as we know it, is very unpredictable."},{"time":4000,"text":"The best minds in the best institutions"},{"time":6000,"text":"generally get it wrong."},{"time":8000,"text":"This is in technology. This is in the area of politics,"},{"time":12000,"text":"where pundits, the CIA, MI6 always get it wrong."},{"time":15000,"text":"And it's clearly in the area of finance."},{"time":18000,"text":"With institutions established to think about the future,"},{"time":20000,"text":"the IMF, the BIS, the Financial Stability Forum, couldn't see what was coming."},{"time":24000,"text":"Over 20,000 economists"},{"time":26000,"text":"whose job it is, competitive entry to get there,"},{"time":28000,"text":"couldn't see what was happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30000,"text":"Globalization is getting more complex."},{"time":32000,"text":"And this change is getting more rapid."},{"time":34000,"text":"The future will be more unpredictable."},{"time":36000,"text":"Urbanization, integration,"},{"time":38000,"text":"coming together, leads to a new renaissance."},{"time":41000,"text":"It did this a thousand years ago."},{"time":43000,"text":"The last 40 years have been extraordinary times."},{"time":46000,"text":"Life expectancy has gone up by about 25 years."},{"time":49000,"text":"It took from the Stone Age to achieve that."},{"time":52000,"text":"Income has gone up for a majority of the world's population,"},{"time":54000,"text":"despite the population going up by about two billion people over this period."},{"time":59000,"text":"And illiteracy has gone down, from a half to about a quarter of the people on Earth."},{"time":62000,"text":"A huge opportunity, unleashing of new potential"},{"time":65000,"text":"for innovation, for development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67000,"text":"But there is an underbelly."},{"time":69000,"text":"There are two Achilles' heels of globalization."},{"time":72000,"text":"There is the Achilles' heel of growing inequality --"},{"time":74000,"text":"those that are left out, those that feel angry,"},{"time":77000,"text":"those that are not participating. Globalization"},{"time":79000,"text":"has not been inclusive."},{"time":81000,"text":"The second Achilles' heel is complexity --"},{"time":84000,"text":"a growing fragility, a growing brittleness."},{"time":88000,"text":"What happens in one place very quickly affects everything else."},{"time":91000,"text":"This is a systemic risk, systemic shock."},{"time":94000,"text":"We've seen it in the financial crisis. We've seen it in the pandemic flu."},{"time":97000,"text":"It will become virulent and it's something we have to build resilience against."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101000,"text":"A lot of this is driven by what's happening in technology."},{"time":104000,"text":"There have been huge leaps. There will be a million-fold improvement"},{"time":107000,"text":"in what you can get for the same price"},{"time":109000,"text":"in computing by 2030."},{"time":111000,"text":"That's what the experience of the last 20 years has been."},{"time":113000,"text":"It will continue."},{"time":115000,"text":"Our computers, our systems will be as primitive"},{"time":118000,"text":"as the Apollo's are for today."},{"time":120000,"text":"Our mobile phones are more powerful than the total Apollo space engine."},{"time":123000,"text":"Our mobile phones are more powerful than"},{"time":125000,"text":"some of the strongest computers of 20 years ago."},{"time":127000,"text":"So what will this do?"},{"time":129000,"text":"It will create huge opportunities in technology."},{"time":132000,"text":"Miniaturization as well."},{"time":134000,"text":"There will be invisible capacity. Invisible capacity in our bodies,"},{"time":137000,"text":"in our brains, and in the air."},{"time":139000,"text":"This is a dust mite on a nanoreplica."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142000,"text":"This sort of ability to do everything in new ways unleashes potential,"},{"time":146000,"text":"not least in the area of medicine."},{"time":148000,"text":"This is a stem cell that we've developed here in Oxford,"},{"time":151000,"text":"from an embryonic stem cell."},{"time":153000,"text":"We can develop any part of the body."},{"time":155000,"text":"Increasingly, over time, this will be possible from our own skin --"},{"time":158000,"text":"able to replicate parts of the body."},{"time":160000,"text":"Fantastic potential for regenerative medicine."},{"time":162000,"text":"I don't think there will be a Special Olympics long after 2030,"},{"time":166000,"text":"because of this capacity to regenerate parts of the body."},{"time":169000,"text":"But the question is, \"Who will have it?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":171000,"text":"The other major development is going to be"},{"time":173000,"text":"in the area of what can happen in genetics."},{"time":175000,"text":"The capacity to create, as this mouse has been genetically modified,"},{"time":181000,"text":"something which goes three times faster,"},{"time":183000,"text":"lasts for three times longer, we could produce,"},{"time":185000,"text":"as this mouse can, to the age of our equivalent of 80 years,"},{"time":189000,"text":"using about the same amount of food."},{"time":192000,"text":"But will this only be available for the super rich,"},{"time":194000,"text":"for those that can afford it? Are we headed for a new eugenics?"},{"time":197000,"text":"Will only those that are able to afford it"},{"time":200000,"text":"be able to be this super race of the future?"},{"time":203000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":204000,"text":"So the big question for us is,"},{"time":206000,"text":"\"How do we manage this technological change?\""},{"time":208000,"text":"How do we ensure that it creates"},{"time":210000,"text":"a more inclusive technology,"},{"time":212000,"text":"a technology which means"},{"time":215000,"text":"that not only as we grow older,"},{"time":217000,"text":"that we can also grow wiser, and that we're able to support"},{"time":219000,"text":"the populations of the future?"},{"time":221000,"text":"One of the most dramatic manifestations of these improvements"},{"time":224000,"text":"will be moving from population pyramids"},{"time":226000,"text":"to what we might term population coffins."},{"time":229000,"text":"There is unlikely to be a pension"},{"time":231000,"text":"or a retirement age in 2030."},{"time":234000,"text":"These will be redundant concepts. And this isn't only something of the West."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237000,"text":"The most dramatic changes will be the skyscraper"},{"time":240000,"text":"type of new pyramids"},{"time":242000,"text":"that will take place in China and in many other countries."},{"time":245000,"text":"So forget about retirements if you're young."},{"time":247000,"text":"Forget about pensions. Think about life and where it's going to be going."},{"time":250000,"text":"Of course, migration will become even more important."},{"time":253000,"text":"The war on talent, the need to attract people"},{"time":255000,"text":"at all skill ranges,"},{"time":257000,"text":"to push us around in our wheelchairs,"},{"time":259000,"text":"but also to drive our economies. Our innovation will be vital."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262000,"text":"The employment in the rich countries"},{"time":264000,"text":"will go down from about 800"},{"time":266000,"text":"to about 700 million of these people."},{"time":268000,"text":"This would imply a massive leap in migration."},{"time":270000,"text":"So the concerns, the xenophobic concerns of today,"},{"time":273000,"text":"of migration, will be turned on their head,"},{"time":275000,"text":"as we search for people to help us sort out"},{"time":278000,"text":"our pensions and our economies in the future."},{"time":280000,"text":"And then, the systemic risks."},{"time":282000,"text":"We understand that these will become much more virulent,"},{"time":285000,"text":"that what we see today"},{"time":287000,"text":"is this interweaving of societies, of systems,"},{"time":290000,"text":"fastened by technologies and hastened by just-in-time management systems."},{"time":295000,"text":"Small levels of stock push resilience into other people's responsibility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300000,"text":"The collapse in biodiversity,"},{"time":302000,"text":"climate change, pandemics, financial crises:"},{"time":305000,"text":"these will be the currency that we will think about."},{"time":308000,"text":"And so a new awareness will have to arise,"},{"time":310000,"text":"of how we deal with these, how we mobilize ourselves,"},{"time":313000,"text":"in a new way, and come together as a community"},{"time":316000,"text":"to manage systemic risk."},{"time":318000,"text":"It's going to require innovation."},{"time":320000,"text":"It's going to require an understanding that the glory of globalization"},{"time":324000,"text":"could also be its downfall."},{"time":326000,"text":"This could be our best century ever because of the achievements,"},{"time":329000,"text":"or it could be our worst."},{"time":331000,"text":"And of course we need to worry about the individuals,"},{"time":333000,"text":"particularly the individuals that feel that they've"},{"time":335000,"text":"been left out in one way or another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337000,"text":"An individual, for the first time in the history of humanity,"},{"time":340000,"text":"will have the capacity, by 2030,"},{"time":342000,"text":"to destroy the planet, to wreck everything,"},{"time":345000,"text":"through the creation, for example, of a biopathogen."},{"time":348000,"text":"How do we begin to weave these tapestries together?"},{"time":350000,"text":"How do we think about complex systems in new ways?"},{"time":353000,"text":"That will be the challenge of the scholars,"},{"time":355000,"text":"and of all of us engaged in thinking about the future."},{"time":358000,"text":"The rest of our lives will be in the future. We need to prepare for it now."},{"time":361000,"text":"We need to understand that the governance structure in the world is fossilized."},{"time":364000,"text":"It cannot begin to cope with the challenges that this will bring."},{"time":368000,"text":"We have to develop a new way of managing the planet,"},{"time":371000,"text":"collectively, through collective wisdom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"We know, and I know from my own experience,"},{"time":375000,"text":"that amazing things can happen,"},{"time":377000,"text":"when individuals and societies come together"},{"time":379000,"text":"to change their future."},{"time":381000,"text":"I left South Africa, and 15 years later,"},{"time":383000,"text":"after thinking I would never go back,"},{"time":385000,"text":"I had the privilege and the honor to work in the government of Nelson Mandela."},{"time":388000,"text":"This was a miracle. We can create miracles,"},{"time":390000,"text":"collectively, in our lifetime."},{"time":392000,"text":"It is vital that we do so."},{"time":394000,"text":"It is vital that the ideas that are nurtured in TED,"},{"time":396000,"text":"that the ideas that we think about"},{"time":398000,"text":"look forward, and make sure that this will be the most glorious century,"},{"time":401000,"text":"and not one of eco-disaster and eco-collapse."},{"time":404000,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}